stimulus:
Instructions

In this experiment, you will read what different people say and rate how natural that sounds. Here's an example from Leah:

Leah: ""I have no idea if Mitchell got a poodle. Did Frank suggest that Mitchell wanted to get a poodle?""

Leah first made a statement and then asked a question. We ask you to rate how natural the question sounds in the context of the statement. You will give your answer on a sliding scale from ""totally unnatural"" to ""totally natural"".

We start off with four practice examples. Then you will rate 30 examples.

Payment: You will be paid $1.35 to participate in this experiment, which will take about 5 minutes to complete.

Consent: By clicking on the button below you agree to participate in this experiment, which is conducted by researchers at the University of Stuttgart. You may withdraw from this experiment at any time without penalty. The data collected will be anonymous and confidential. If you have any questions, you may contact the requester through Prolific's platform, or directly at judith.tonhauser@ling.uni-stuttgart.de.

First practice example

Katia: ""I have no idea where Natalie is from. Is Natalie from the USA?""

Good response!

Katia: ""I have no idea where Natalie is from. Is Natalie from the USA?""

Katia's question sounds very natural in this context because it is natural for Katia to ask whether Natalie is from the USA if Katia doesn't know where Natalie is from.

Here's the second practice example.

Xenia: ""I don't have any sisters. Have you met my sister yet?""

Good response!

Xenia: ""I don't have any sisters. Have you met my sister yet?""

Xenia's question does not sound very natural in this context. Her question implies that she has a sister, but she stated that she doesn't have any sisters.

Here's the third practice example.

Kerstin: ""I am going on vacation to Ireland. Does Fritz realize that Joe is going with me?""

Good response!

Kerstin: ""I am going on vacation to Ireland. Does Fritz realize that Joe is going with me?""

Kerstin's question sounds very natural in this context.

Here's the last practice example.

Mirko: ""I have no idea if Anna has any dogs. Is Samuel glad that Anna fed her dogs?""

Incorrect response

Mirko: ""I have no idea if Anna has any dogs. Is Samuel glad that Anna fed her dogs?""

Mirko's question does not sound very natural in this context. Mirko's question implies that Anna has dogs, but he stated that he doesn't know whether Anna has any dogs. Please repeat the fourth practice example.

Here's the last practice example.

Mirko: ""I have no idea if Anna has any dogs. Is Samuel glad that Anna fed her dogs?""

Good response!

Mirko: ""I have no idea if Anna has any dogs. Is Samuel glad that Anna fed her dogs?""

Mirko's question does not sound very natural in this context. Mirko's question implies that he thinks that Anna has dogs, but he stated that he doesn't know whether Anna has any dogs.

Great, you're ready to go!
To make sure you are paying attention, we have included some examples for which we know the right answer. If you read the examples carefully, you will definitely get those right.
Ashley: ""Emma is in law school. Did Justin confirm that Emma studied on Saturday morning?""
Leia: ""I don't know if Ann plays any instrument. Does Ann play the flute, too?""
Scott: ""I don't know if Mary is pregnant. Did Patrick say that Mary is pregnant?""
Cici: ""I don't know if Stephen was ever in the habit of vaping. Has Stephen recently stopped vaping?""
Rachel: ""Emily has been saving for a year. Did Brian demonstrate that Emily bought a car yesterday?""
Arlen: ""I don't know if anyone was playing outside with the kids. Was it Jack who was playing outside with the kids?""
Sharon: ""Jayden doesn't have a driver's license. Did Stephanie suggest that Jayden rented a car?""
Brandon: ""Grace loves her sister. Did Andrew discover that Grace visited her sister?""
Nicole: ""I don't know if Jon walks to work. Did Ruth announce that Jon walks to work?""
Virginia: ""I don't know if Sophia got a tattoo. Is Ben annoyed that Sophia got a tattoo?""
Elizabeth: ""Olivia has two small children. Did Jerry acknowledge that Olivia sleeps until noon?""
Pax: ""Hendrick was looking to buy a car. Was Hendrick's car expensive?""
Finn: ""I don't know if Samantha has a new hat. Does Samantha have a new hat?""
Dalton: ""I don't know if Svenja plays any sport. Does Svenja also play soccer?""
Dorothy: ""I don't know if Isabella ate a steak on Sunday. Did Kevin see that Isabella ate a steak on Sunday?""
Jonathan: ""I don't know if Charley speaks Spanish. Did Anna prove that Charley speaks Spanish?""
Paul: ""I don't know if Owen shoveled snow last winter. Did Cynthia inform Sam that Owen shoveled snow last winter?""
Scott: ""I don't know if Frank got a cat. Did Melissa establish that Frank got a cat?""
Saskia: ""I don't know if William was ever interested in history. Is William interested in history again?""
Eric: ""I don't know if Josh learned to ride a bike yesterday. Does Sharon think that Josh learned to ride a bike yesterday?""
Dorothy: ""I don't know if Zoe calculated the tip. Did Tim hear that Zoe calculated the tip?""
Margaret: ""I don't know if Josie went on vacation to France. Does Scott know that Josie went on vacation to France?""
Melissa: ""I don't know if Jackson ran 10 miles. Is Laura right that Jackson ran 10 miles?""
Marlo: ""I don't know if this pizza has mushrooms on it. Does this pizza have mushrooms on it?""
Jessica: ""Tony has been sober for 20 years. Did Rebecca confess that Tony had a drink last night?""
Michelle: ""Julian is Cuban. Did Kathleen admit that Julian dances salsa?""
Ike: ""Mary visited her aunt yesterday. Is Mary's aunt sick?""
Autumn: ""I don't know if John was ever reading ""Dune"". Has John recently continued reading ""Dune""?""
Joseph: ""I don't know if Mia drank 2 cocktails last night. Did Ray pretend that Mia drank 2 cocktails last night?""
Joseph: ""Danny is a diabetic. Did Amanda reveal that Danny ate the last cupcake?""
NA
You're done! Thanks for participating!
